%Alu and L1 have often been cited as having the potential to contribute to alternative isoforms of a gene. Both Alu and L1 contain splice donor and acceptor sites and therefore can alter splice signals. Moreover, L1, and in some cases Alu, can cause premature adenylation through the polyadenylation signals located within the sequence. For these reasons, it was important to examine the linear decay of Alu and L1 in genes that are alternatively spliced.
